							Nu Skin Company						













Daniel R. Chard of Nu Skin Enterprises

October 6, 2012 ·							by nuskincompany ·							in Daniel R. Chard, Nu Skin 


Daniel R. Chard is currently the president of global sales and operations for Nu Skin. Before he was promoted to this position, he served as president of the same cosmetics company’s European division. He has an extensive background in marketing and product management along with executive experience in several other corporations.
Educational Background
Chard holds an undergraduate degree in economics from BYU and an MBA from the University of Minnesota. His early work experience includes a marketing manager position at the Pillsbury corporation and marketing director at PUR Recovery Engineering. Prior to joining Nu Skin Enterprises, he also worked in the executive marketing departments for Pharmanex and Big Planet.
Primary Roles at Nu Skin
As part of his current position at Nu Skin, Daniel R. Chard manages the company’s global marketing strategies. He also coordinates various special events, manages the distributor commission program and helps to identify new target markets for Nu Skin’s product lines. Before being promoted to president of global sales and operations, he was in charge of putting together a program for helping Nu Skin sellers and distributors reach their performance goals.
The Distributor Success Process
Chard oversees this training and compensation program to help each Nu Skin seller succeed even with little prior sales experience. Distributors are rewarded different statuses on a scale according to their sales numbers, and each tier comes with various rewards in addition to monetary compensation. Sellers are first introduced to Nu Skin’s products and encouraged to share the benefits of them with their friends and family. They also receive extensive training in methods for building solid distributor networks.
Nu Skin’s distributor success process has been developed on the principle that hard work brings the desired rewards. New distributors get started by purchasing their starter product packages and meeting all established requirements for earning bonuses and sales commissions. Nu Skin distributors also learn how to recruit others as product sellers for the company.
Chard’s marketing experience and approach are evident in the distributor success program due to the company resources available to each distributor. Sellers at every level get a good amount of support from Nu Skin, and they also receive all the detailed information they need to make successful sales. Nu Skin’s products are subject to periodic clinical trials to determine their effectiveness, and he makes sure this data is available for distributors to use for their sales presentations.
During Daniel R. Chard’s time as Nu Skin global operations and management president, the company has grown in both geographic markets and numbers of sellers. One of Nu Skin’s newest overseas target markets is mainland China. The company has direct selling licenses in more than 50 different regional territories and is expected to add more of them in the near future. These include North America, Asia, Latin America, Africa and various countries throughout Europe. Another notable part of Nu Skin under Chard’s leadership is the company’s Force for Good philanthropic program, which helps to provide health care and educational opportunities to citizens of developing countries.

 

